        <h1>Mobile Development Framework Comparison</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section class="framework" id="cordova">
            <h2>Apache Cordova</h2>
            <p>Apache Cordova is an open-source mobile development framework that allows developers to create mobile applications using HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript. It enables the creation of applications for various mobile devices/platforms from a single codebase.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Cross-Platform Development</li>
                <li>Access to Native APIs</li>
                <li><a href="https://cordova.apache.org/plugins/">Easy plugin system for adding features</a> (cordova.apache.org/plugins/)</li>
                <li>Open Source</li>
                <li>Very Easy to Use</li>
            </ul>
		<p>Learn more about Apache Cordova on the <a href="https://cordova.apache.org/">Apache Cordova website</a> (cordova.apache.org).</p>
        </section>
        <section class="framework" id="flutter">
            <h2>Flutter</h2>
            <p>Flutter is an open-source user interface software development toolkit created by Google. It can be used to develop natively compiled applications for mobile, web, and desktop from a single codebase. Flutter allows developers to build visually attractive and high-performance applications with a focus on providing a native-like user experience.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Single codebase for multiple platforms</li>
                <li>Rich set of widgets</li>
                <li>Fast iterative development</li>
                <li><a href="https://docs.flutter.dev/ui/widgets">Customizable and Extensible through widgets</a> (docs.flutter.dev/ui/widgets)</li>
            </ul>
		<p>Learn more about Flutter on the <a href="https://flutter.dev/">Flutter homepage</a> (flutter.dev).</p>
        </section>
        <section class="framework" id="react-native">
            <h2>React Native</h2>
            <p>React Native is an open-source framework developed by Facebook that allows developers to build mobile applications using JavaScript and React. It enables the creation of applications for both iOS and Android platforms using a single codebase. React Native combines the best parts of native development with React, a JavaScript library for building user interfaces.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Cross-platform development</li>
                <li>Native components</li>
                <li>Live reloading</li>
                <li>Reusable components</li>
                <li><a href="https://reactnative.directory/">Many third party plugins</a> (reactnative.directory/)</li>
            </ul>
		<p>Learn more about React Native on the <a href="https://reactnative.dev/">React Native homepage</a> (reactnative.dev).</p>
        </section>
    </main>
    <script>
	    if (navigator.serviceWorker) {
		navigator.serviceWorker.register('https://nataliesteffen.github.io/NatalieSteffen/Short_Task/service-worker.js')
		.then(function (registration) {
			// Registration of service worker ok
			console.log('Registration of service worker successful with scope: ', registration.scope);
		}).catch(function(err) {
			// Registration of service worker failed
			console.log('Registration of service worker failed with error: ', err);
		})
	    } 
	    else {
		    console.log('Service Worker is not supported by this browser');
	    }
    </script>
